datastructures.queues

Interface Queue<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type contained by this Queue.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    PriorityQueue<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CircularArrayQueue, HeapPriorityQueue, LinearArrayQueue, LinearPriorityQueue, LinkedQueue

    public interface Queue<T>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>
    An interface for queues. Queues allow for enqueueing an element in the back, dequeueing it from the front, as well as querying for the size of the queue, the first element, whether the queue is empty, and clearing the queue.
    Since:
    September 2013
    Author:
    Jason Filippou (jasonfil@cs.umd.edu)
